{"questionId":"11777","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Kayla wants to measure the extent to which two judges in a gymnastics competition are in agreement. Each judge has ranked the seven competitors, as shown in the table, where 1 is the highest ranking and 7 is the lowest.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/10cdcbda7941d43f481ea6b0dcb72f9a7f8b8449.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Calculate Spearman’s rank correlation coefficient for this data.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>average equal ranks &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><img src=\"__IMG__/eb86cc640b4d491a6dc4decda9c24423ee7d03ab.png\">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em><em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{r_s} = 0.817\">\n  <mrow>\n    <msub>\n      <mi>r</mi>\n      <mi>s</mi>\n    </msub>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>0.817</mn>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A2</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>[5 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"11777","referenceCode":"EXM.1.SL.TZ0.2a","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Calculate Spearman’s rank correlation coefficient for this data.","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 5]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.10—Spearman’s rank correlation coefficient"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}